				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Our pets do need a major upgrade but it needs ot be done in a way such as to not overpower us in the solo area like necros are these days and we also need something to make us more wanted as a class.
<br />
One idea is if we have spent the AA to train our higher elemental forms like Heart of Stone let it also act like an inbuilt stackable pet focus for all earth pets and the same applies for all of our pets and the other higher elemental forms if we train then.
<br />
Not an uber pet focus but something to make the AA worthwhile since we cannot use them while on a mount.
<br />
Also our pets could perhaps be made so they enhance our group.
<br />
For example make it so if say I had a lvl 70 Child of Earth up it would buff the AC and HP up for the entire group like if everyone had Elemental Form: Earth 3 on.
<br />
The same would apply to any of our pets as long as we have the higher elemental form for that pet type trained and the same pet of that type is out.
<br />

<br />
Another thing is that they need to give our earth pet snare as an alternate to use since some classes already have snare for their pets I dont see why we have to suffer as a class. They could set it up so its a command like /pet snare or /pet root and this idea could even be used to fix the fire pet somewhat maybe by letting use change it say by /pet spells  and /pet lifetap which would give the fire pet the ability to drain a mob of health instead of casting its spells.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Edit: If lifetap is ruled out for fire pet how about a slow proc then ? Not as powerful as player casted of course but something to make the pet worth using.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by varlash on Mon Mar 07, 2005 3:39 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
