				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm a little curious where the suggested changes for Ancient: Nova Strike came from, namely the damage of 2850.  Additionally, the damage mana ratio is unprecedented at 5.38.
<br />

<br />
I'll confess I'm an Evocation mage, bolt and rain slinger, with all the biases inherent.
<br />

<br />
I can understand the rationale for making it a higher damage than the 66 Bolt of Jerikor, in that an Ancient should be an Ancient...but past history from the 61-65 nukes shows a pattern:
<br />

<br />
61 Firebolt of Tallon (2000 dmg / 500 mana, Evocation, 4 dmg / mana)
<br />
65 Ancient: Chaos Vortex (1860 dmg / 468 mana, Conjuration, 3.97 dmg / mana)
<br />

<br />
Current 66-70:
<br />

<br />
66 Bolt of Jerikor (2751 dmg / 625 mana, Evocation,  4.4 Dmg / mana)
<br />
70 Ancient: Nova Strike (2302 dmg / 517 mana, Conjuration, 4.45 dmg / mana)
<br />

<br />
What happened from PoP/GoD to OoW is: 66 BoJ got better proportionally, or 70 ANS didn't get better. 
<br />

<br />
65 ACV is 93% the dmg of 61 FBoT, and about the same % on the mana ratio.
<br />

<br />
However, 70 ANS is only 83% of the dmg of 66 BoJ, and similar on the mana %.
<br />

<br />
What would keep 70 ANS in line with ACV/FBoT would be to use a 93% scaling factor, making a revised version:
<br />

<br />
70 Ancient: Nova Strike (2558 / 574 mana, Conjuration, 4.45 Dmg / mana).
<br />

<br />
Originally, I had 585 mana, as I was using the 93% scale...but when I computed the dmg / mana ratios, I had ANS at 4.37...less than the bolt.  Back to the drawing board, I plugged in the 4.45, and came out with the 574 mana cost.
<br />

<br />
Now, if we were to be bold enough to request a 5.38 dmg / mana ratio, an alternate version of ANS would be: 2558 damage / 476 mana.
<br />

<br />
My suggestion presumes the continued use of evocation as a bolt/rain skill, where the highest potential damage is the goal, and conjuration as a DD/everything else and enjoys the best mana efficiency while sacrificing the highest burst damage of a mage; the best at sustained damage.
<br />

<br />
Granted, my bias is that I think specializations are a good thing, so that you have druids deciding whether they are alteration or evocation (or whatever their choices are between nuking and healing), and with us, we decide between best mana efficiency or highest per-nuke-damage.  I like the fact that there are some things in EQ that are not "must-have" or "must-do"....cookie-cutter characters that are all identical are bland, imho.
<br />

<br />
As a concession to the conjuration mages, the only way I would support the 2850 / 530 proposed ANS would be if all mage nukes (bolts, rains, DDs) were made into conjuration OR an Ancient bolt were added with a % increase in damage over BoJ commensurate with the increase of ANS over 70 Star Strike (2132 dmg).  Assuming 2132 and 2850 as the DD versions, a 26% increase is seen, putting an appropriately scaled Ancient Bolt at 3679.
<br />

<br />
I'm open to intelligent discussion about changing mage nukes to all be conjuration, or to preserving the choice between evocation and specialization.  Of course, I got 10pp on some (I use this term loosely) "person" saying something derogatory and ultimately unproductive against evocation mages.
<br />

<br />
/wry smirk<br />_________________<br />Dyrauelene
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">We the willing, led by the unknowing, are doing the impossible for the ungrateful. We have done so much for so long with so little, that we are now qualified to do anything with nothing.</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
