<br />
 
<br />
All the DD's are higher level than the Bolt and a natural assumption is that higher level spells are more powerful than lower level spells. That is clearly not the case for Mages. With the lack of line of sight issues then the DD's not only need increasing in damage a little but also need increasing more so in mana efficiency to make them clearly superior in that regard compared to the bolt. The Ancient should also be clearly superior to any previous magician direct damage spell (it is an Ancient afterall).
<br />
 
<br />
Rough figures (assuing the bolt stays at 2751 damage, 4.4 efficiency) for the DD's would be
<br />
 
<br />
Blade Strike 2k damage, 4.5 efficiency
<br />
Star Strike 2.3k damage, 4.65 efficiency
<br />
Ancient 2.6k damage, 4.8 efficiency
<br />
 
<br />
The bolt would still remain the largest single damaging spell, though with the Ancients shorter cast time it would be close to the same dps if chain casting but would have 10% better efficiency.
<br />
 
<br />
The lvl 70 DD's really need to offer a significant gain in at least some regard compared to the Bolt; something that they currently don't, not even in the Ancient's case.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=653282" target=_blank>Casala</a>
