<br />
Not sure where the 2850 figure came from for ANcient DD (from Itchyban I think originally), or where the mana efficiency came from.
<br />

<br />
I do think that the figures posted in the Top 10 are pretty silly in the context of the current game (regarding balance between mage and wiz nukes).
<br />

<br />
Rough figures I think are more appropriate (assuing the bolt stays at 2751 damage, 4.4 efficiency) for the DD's would be
<br />
 
<br />
Blade Strike 2k damage, 4.5 efficiency
<br />
Star Strike 2.3k damage, 4.65 efficiency
<br />
Ancient 2.6k damage, 4.8 efficiency
<br />

<br />
The Bolt would remain the biggest DD but the Conjuration DD's would have the edge on efficiency (specialisation aside, but thats a choice each mage has to make) with the Ancient been considerably more efficient and approaching the bolt dps.
<br />

<br />
Of course the bolt would still have the sizeable advantage of been Lvl 66 so easy to obtain (compared to the Lvl 70 and Ancient DD) and that all pre OoW foci work for full on it. Attaining top end foci that work to Lvl 70 is a huge issue even for the highest end raiders.
<br />

<br />
Note that I think that the changes here are what need to be made purely to balance the DD's with the bolt currently. Anything that changes due to class 're-envisioning' would result in further changes been made, not that I think anything will come from class re-envisioning.
<br />

<br />
Another thing I think would have made sense would have to switched the levels of Blade Strike and Starstrike so that the Fire DD was at 68 and the magic DD at 70. Reason been that discounting GOD Ancient then you are upgrading Sun Vortex to StarStrike, thats a big gap. Magic wise you are upgrading Rock of Taelosia to BladeStrike, a far smaller upgrade. It would have seemed nice for non-Ancient DD progression to go:
<br />

<br />
Magic (Black Steel), Fire (Sun Vortex), Magic (Rock), Fire (Starstrike at 68), Magic (BladeStrike at 70). With the GOD and OoW Ancients been the same as now aswell as the bolts staying the same.
