			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I was thinking about this today and pondered on the idea of a quested pet focus augment / item. I thought that it would be pretty awesome to maybe have a new quest added onto the Temple of Solusek Ro quest. Something along the lines of combining the shovel, torch, broom and stein into a new all around low Focus for 4 to 49 pets but then being able to quest and get it slowly upgraded in power, maybe up to the Minion of Eternity focus or higher. Possibly even maxing out at chaos level or have a cool right clicky for our pet on it...burnout, a DS, velocity, summon companion, shrink, etc. It would not only give us mages a fun alternative to raids and missions but give us a new option for upgradeability. 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I agree 100%. The only catch is that some of the original focus items are used as epic 1.0 turn-ins, so they might need to work around that a bit.
<br />

<br />
Another option I was thinking of comes from EQ2, Pet Scaling. I know there are already issues with how pets scale within the various foci, but I think the larger issue as it relates to dps and pet usage is that we're using the same pet for a very long time at higher levels with no real improvement as we level up.
<br />

<br />
IMO, it would be nice to see the 61 Air pet scale with each level of the magician up to level 65 (same goes for the other pets as well), then the level 66 air pet scale up to level 70. The foci would enhance the pets beyond this point. 
<br />

<br />
As a practical example, I will see a relative power decrease as I move from level 63 to level 64, in that I don't get a new pet, my old pet stays the same, yet the mobs I need to fight get a bit stronger. Yes, my nukes do scale a bit, but I would rather see the pet get stronger.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, the pet "system" in EQ1 doesn't provide a lot of support for this idea, in that the devs have to create actual pet objects for each and every combination of level and foci. In other words, if we want the air pet to scale for 5 levels and there are 5 levels of foci (6 if you count unfocused), that would be 30 pet objects that would need to be created just for the level 61 air pet. 
<br />

<br />
So yeah, I think a basic quested focus item of DPoC quality is pretty much a necessity at this point.
<br />

<br />
PS. Give us root.<br />_________________<br />Naladini
