				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">lol, that's why i said it was from eq2 at the beginning of my post <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Honestly though, it would have been nice if they had implemented that style of change back when the "pet balancing improvements" were made a few years ago, because it would have carried through to the higher levels by precedent. They already had the exact pet variance built that we needed, but they were summoned randomly instead of being based on our level.
<br />

<br />
Granted, it was nice to ding to a new level and be able to summon a yellow conning pet all the time, but the drawback to being a mage is that you tend to get stuck in the same hunting spots until you get new pet spells because you're usually limited to fighting creatures that your pet is able to effectively tank. If the pets always scaled by the casters' level, then you'd have more fighting choices available as you level up.<br />_________________<br />Naladini
